Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need
to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved), discard the core and seeds, then thinly slice.
Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed), halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and sliced pepper to the pan.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the peppers have softened and
the chicken is golden all over, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add the onion to the pan and continue to stir-fry until the onion is softened and
the chicken is cooked, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, mix the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @North Indian style spice mix{1}
and half the @mango chutney{40%g} together in a #small bowl{}. Once the chicken is
cooked, stir the mixture into the pan until well combined. Cook until everything
begins to caramelise, ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} on the middle shelf of your #oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

To assemble, lay out the tortillas (3 per person) and share out half the @mayonnaise{1}
in the centre of each one. Add the baby gem lettuce and mango chutney chicken, then
drizzle over any leftover @mayonnaise{1} and @mango chutney{40%g}. Fold over one end
to encase the filling and roll up. Serve with the potato wedges on the side. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've opted to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh, cook in
> the same way.